            text: 'While NaProTechnology was developed at the Saint Paul VI Institute (a Catholic institution), the medical techniques used in RRM (including excision surgery for endometriosis, hormonal evaluation and support, and diagnostic imaging) are standard medical practices used across all healthcare settings. The research supporting RRM outcomes has been published in mainstream peer-reviewed journals including BMC Pregnancy and Childbirth and Fertility and Sterility. Many RRM practitioners are motivated by both clinical evidence and ethical commitments. This is not unique to RRM. All medical practice involves values-based decisions. The relevant question is whether the treatments are effective and whether patients receive complete informed consent.',
